Police in Nairobi have impounded a trailer carrying more than 5,400 undeclared car tyres. A trader based in Eastleigh had declared 1,800 pieces but hid three smaller tyres in each piece The trailer was impounded on Tuesday by officers from the Directorate of Criminal Investigations, in collaboration with Kenya Revenue Authority and the Anti-Counterfeit Agency and other agencies, as part of the crackdown on counterfeits and contraband. Police say they are interrogating several individuals in connection with the tax evasion scheme. The tyres, imported by Global Africa Tyres, were declared to have originated from Batais Trading Company in Dubai.  